shared_text:
Educational Research Institute
July 24 at 5:03 PM ·

Educational Research Institute (ERI) is pleased to announce their success in securing almost 3 million dollars ($2,775,000) from the 2020-2021 CTE Perkins Reserve Grant. In this grant, there were multiple districts submitting as a collaboration. The following districts were awarded: Lasara ISD, San Isidro ISD, San Perlita ISD, La Feria ISD, Santa Rosa ISD, Rio Hondo ISD, Jim Hogg ISD, San Diego ISD, and Benavides ISD.

The acquisition of these grant funds will be utilized to foster innovation through the identification and promotion of promising and proven CTE programs, practices, and strategies that prepare students for non-traditional fields.

If your school would like to receive grants funds like these, please feel free to give our office a call at (956) 365-4100.

All senior boys and girls need to gather all athletic uniforms they still have so they can turn them in when they come to the Last Bell at 3:00-4:30 pm. on Thursday, May 21. Place the uniforms in a plastic bag, tie it up and write your name and what you’re turning in. Ex. Bob - track, baseball.
Also all Seniors must turn in Chromebooks to the elementary between 8:00 and 4:00 pm.
All uniforms And Chromebooks need to be turned in, in order to walk at graduation on Friday.

Graduations at E.C Lerma Stadium on Friday, May 22, 2020 at 7pm.
Two Adults ages 18 and over will be allowed per graduate.
Graduations will not be open to the public.
Federal and state social distancing guidelines must be followed.
Face masks must be worn.

3-5 people per vehicle may park by the fence around the stadium, must practice social distancing.
Graduations will be streamed on Facebook Live
